latestPosts.caption:
#GraziaLifestyle Sweet, festive, and oh-so-delicious! These Christmas cookie bars are the perfect treat to get you in the holiday spirit 🎄🍪

Ingredients:
1 cup plain flour
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1/4 teaspoon salt
125g unsalted butter softened
1/2 cup brown sugar lightly packed
1/4 cup white sugar
1 egg room temperature
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
165g bag Christmas m&ms
1/4 cup Christmas coloured sprinkles plus more for topping

Method:
Preheat oven to 180c. Grease a square baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine plain flour, baking soda, and salt.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, brown sugar, and white sugar.
Add in egg and vanilla extract, and beat for a further 1-2 minutes until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture until combined.
Mix in most of the bag of m&ms, (reserving some for topping) followed by sprinkles until just combined.
Scoop mixture into pan, and top with additional m&ms and sprinkles.
Bake for 15-20 minutes, until golden on the top. Use a skewer to test if it’s baked in the middle.

📽️: @nutrition.with.tessa
